%N A393768 Main diagonal of rectangular array A393760.
%C A393768 The n-th row o.g.f. R(n,x) of rectangle A393760 satisfies: [x^m] exp( m^2*(m + n)*x - m*R(n,x) ) = 0 for m >= 1, n >= 0. This sequence is the main diagonal a(n) = A393760(n, n+1) for n >= 0.
%H A393768 Paul D. Hanna, <a href="/A393768/b393768.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..201</a>
%F A393768 a(n) ~ c * d^n * n^(2*n + 1/2) / exp(2*n), where d = 36.47634888601519724695... and c = 4.4928520452446669... - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Mar 02 2026
%e A393768 Rectangular array A393760 begins
%e A393768   n = 0: [1,  9,  552,  85842,  24653700, ...];
%e A393768   n = 1: [2, 16, 1020, 165536,  49320160, ...];
%e A393768   n = 2: [3, 25, 1692, 289538,  90173820, ...];
%e A393768   n = 3: [4, 36, 2604, 471456, 153941040, ...];
%e A393768   n = 4: [5, 49, 3792, 726674, 248954740, ...];
%e A393768   ...
%e A393768 where the n-th row o.g.f. R(n,x) satisfies:
%e A393768 [x^m] exp( m^2*(m + n)*x - m*R(n,x) ) = 0 for m >= 1, n >= 0.
%e A393768 The main diagonal in the above table forms this sequence.
%o A393768 (PARI) {A393760(n,k) = my(A=[0], m); for(i=1, k+1, m=#A; A=concat(A, 0); A[m+1] = Vec( exp(m^2*(m + n)*x - m*Ser(A)) )[m+1]/m ); polcoef( Ser(A), k)}
%o A393768 for(n=0, 15, print1(A393760(n, n+1),", "))
